dc_description_s: These data layers represent public land survey system (PLSS) corners for Sauk County, Wisconsin in 2018. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, 'Sauk_PLSS_2018.gdb'. The feature layers included in this geodatabase are 'Sauk_PLSSCorners_2018', 'Sauk_PLSSQuarterSection_2018', 'Sauk_PLSSSection_2018', and 'Sauk_PLSSTownship_2018'. [PLSSCorners: The current control point on the surface of the earth and its associated current coordinate value, generally determined by a surveying process and used to define an extremity of a boundary.PLSSQuarterSection: The second division of the PLSS and commonly called a quarter section.PLSSSection: The first division of the PLSS and commonly called a section.PLSSTownship: In the Public Land Survey System a Township refers to a unit of land, that is nominally six miles on a side, usually containing 36 sections.]
